						<summary>

						<p>Outer <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Mantrapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Perumāḷ Sundarapāṇḍya: year 4.</hi></p>						

						<p>This epigraph may be assigned to c. 13th century on palaeographical considerations.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register some gift by the communities like <hi rend="italic">vaṇṇār</hi> (washerman), <hi rend="italic">nāvidar</hi> (barber), <hi rend="italic">paḷḷar, paṟaiyar,</hi> etc to provide for the services to the deity Uśāttāṉam-uḍaiyār. The order <hi rend="italic">(ōlai)</hi> issued to this effect on the fourth year of his reign was attested by one of his officers named [Muṉaiyada]raiyan. The writing at the end of lines in the right of the inscription has been erased by chiselling. Hence, the details of the royal order are not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
